				<td colspan="2"><span>We need a good guide written that explains in detail how to do all the commands etc.
<br />

<br />
I have been reluctant to do all that with the Molto channel for several reasons:
<br />

<br />
1)  I want the channel to be open to visitors.
<br />
2)  I don't want extra hassle.
<br />
3)  I don't know the commands.  How do you pass moderatorship when you log off?  Can you have an established list of moderators so you don't have to do that?  What if none of those people are on?  Do you pass it to just anyone?  Does there HAVE to be a moderator on the channel for it to exist?
<br />

<br />
Tons of questions.
<br />

<br />
If someone with real experience in moderating channels etc. could make a guide for us, that would be sweet.  Sadiki made one of sorts, at least a listing of some commands.  I kept it in our &quot;forum of preservation&quot; on the old site so we would not lose the resource.  But I'm afraid it was not informative enough for me to feel comfortable starting that sort of thing with the Molto Channel.
