				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Serverwide Bards = spam<a name="23759"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 25 04 10:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Takes a certain amount of dedication to protect a channel like that.  Absent a conscious transfer of moderator status, when the moderator logs or goes LD, the person who's been in the channel the longest gets mod status by default.
<br />

<br />
On the nameless, we had a trade channel for auctions, before the bazaar.  Generally regarded as a public channel.  Some folks got their jollies by camping it for days until they became mods by default, then purporting to regulate the channel.  So, if you ended an auction in &quot;PST,&quot; for example, they'd kick you.  Or they'd password the channel for a while, then unpassword it.
<br />

<br />
Point simply is - unless the people trying to manage and protect the channel are on a whole lot, the annoying ones can always seize the channel given enough patience.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
